casConfigMaxCalledDigits.name: casConfigMaxCalledDigits
casConfigMaxCalledDigits.description: Maximum number of expected DNIS digits (called number) in an incoming call.

casConfigMaxCallingDigits.name: casConfigMaxCallingDigits
casConfigMaxCallingDigits.description: Maximum number of expected ANI digits (calling number) in an incoming call. Used in India.

casConfigReqCallingNumber.name: casConfigReqCallingNumber
casConfigReqCallingNumber.description: Request calling number from remote end.

casConfigCallingNumberMandatory.name: casConfigCallingNumberMandatory
casConfigCallingNumberMandatory.description: Calling Number is mandatory on incoming calls. When not available, incoming call will be rejected.

casConfigRingBack.name: casConfigRingBack
casConfigRingBack.description: Enable audible ring back to remote end.

casConfigCdBits.name: casConfigCdBits
casConfigCdBits.description: Country specific pattern for signaling bits C and D.

casConfigAssumeAcceptCall.name: casConfigAssumeAcceptCall
casConfigAssumeAcceptCall.description: Assume all R2 calls will be accepted regardless of calling/called numbers. This parameter is used after inWaitAccept timer expires with no response from security server.

casConfigOOS.name: casConfigOOS
casConfigOOS.description: Indicates the state of the channel. If true, the channel is in out-of-service state. If false, the channel is in-service

casConfigBusyOutOOS.name: casConfigBusyOutOOS
casConfigBusyOutOOS.description: Determines a channel's appearance when in out-of-service state. If true, the channel appears busy (off-hook). If false, the channel remains on-hook, but will not answer calls

casConfigWinkAfterAnswer.name: casConfigWinkAfterAnswer
casConfigWinkAfterAnswer.description: Wink After Answer, when active, will drop an incoming call for 100 msec. Used in some countries (Brazil) to reject collect calls.

casConfigSkipCategoryRequest.name: casConfigSkipCategoryRequest
casConfigSkipCategoryRequest.description: Do not request the caller's category on an incoming call, set speech condition. Used in Korea.

casTimersHitThresh.description: The amount of time a signaling bit pattern must be stable before it is considered to have changed value.

casTimersInSeizeHold.name: casTimersInSeizeHold
casTimersInSeizeHold.description: The minimum duration of an incoming off-hook pattern to be considered a valid line seizure.

casTimersOutSeizeHold.name: casTimersOutSeizeHold
casTimersOutSeizeHold.description: The minimum duration of off-hook signal to seize line for an outgoing call

casTimersOutWaitConnect.name: casTimersOutWaitConnect
casTimersOutWaitConnect.description: The maximum delay before receiving a connect indication

casTimersOutConnectHold.name: casTimersOutConnectHold
casTimersOutConnectHold.description: The minimum duration of an off-hook pattern to be considered a valid connect indication

casTimersLocalRelease.name: casTimersLocalRelease
casTimersLocalRelease.description: The maximum delay to release local system resources

casTimersLineRelease.name: casTimersLineRelease
casTimersLineRelease.description: When locally releasing a call, the maximum delay before receiving a line-release indication

casTimersLineReleaseHold.name: casTimersLineReleaseHold
casTimersLineReleaseHold.description: The minimum duration of an on-hook pattern to be considered a valid line-release indication

casTimersRecover.name: casTimersRecover
casTimersRecover.description: The minimum duration of 'blind' period after each incoming or outgoing call

casTimersWaitR2Digit.name: casTimersWaitR2Digit
casTimersWaitR2Digit.description: The maximum waiting period for an incoming R2 digit, before dropping the call.

casTimersInWaitAccept.name: casTimersInWaitAccept
casTimersInWaitAccept.description: The maximum waiting period for the CVX to process calling/called numbers before proceeding with the R2 call sequence accepting or rejecting an incoming call.

casTimersInWaitAnswer.name: casTimersInWaitAnswer
casTimersInWaitAnswer.description: The maximum waiting period before the CVX answers an incoming call.

casTimersOutWaitAnswer.name: casTimersOutWaitAnswer
casTimersOutWaitAnswer.description: The maximum waiting period before the remote end answers the CVX's outbound call.

casTimersInCongestionPulseDuration.name: casTimersInCongestionPulseDuration
casTimersInCongestionPulseDuration.description: Duration of the congestion A-4 pulse. This backward pulse is sent on incoming calls, when no response is received for an excessive period of time.

casTimersInSetupCompleteHold.name: casTimersInSetupCompleteHold
casTimersInSetupCompleteHold.description: Delay between reception of last inbound digit and begin ringing (Q.471/Q.475). For New Zealand, this parameter should be set to 1900 msec.

casTimersInAnswerToWinkDelay.name: casTimersInAnswerToWinkDelay
casTimersInAnswerToWinkDelay.description: After an incoming call is answered, an optional wink may be sent to the switch, to reject collect a call. This parameter specifies how long to wait, after the call is answered, before transmitting a wink.

casTimersInAfterAnswerWinkPulse.name: casTimersInAfterAnswerWinkPulse
casTimersInAfterAnswerWinkPulse.description: Duration of the wink sent after an incoming call is answered. This optional wink pulse is used in Brazil to filter incoming collect calls.

casTimersOutLineAbnormalReleaseHold.name: casTimersOutLineAbnormalReleaseHold
casTimersOutLineAbnormalReleaseHold.description: Hold period for an abnormal line release condition on an outbound call.

casTimersOutLocalReleaseDelay.name: casTimersOutLocalReleaseDelay
casTimersOutLocalReleaseDelay.description: Delay between the local disconnect on outbound calls, and the transmission of the local line release bits.

hSSIConfigHSSIQueueDepth.description: Internal queue depth for data to be transmitted by HSSI. Once queue depth is reached, data will be dropped until queue depth empties beyond this value. Data dropped is clipped from end of queue.

l2FHomeGatewayHostName.description: Fully Qualified Domain Name (DNS name) of L2F Home Gateway

l2FHomeGatewaySendName.description: Name to send as the NAS name in the L2F CONF packet to open a tunnel

l2FHomeGatewaySendPassword.description: Password to send to the Home Gateway when sending the L2F OPEN packet to open a tunnel

l2FHomeGatewayReceiveName.name: l2FHomeGatewayReceiveName
l2FHomeGatewayReceiveName.description: Name to expect from the Home Gateway in the received L2F CONF packet when opening a tunnel. If left blank, then the Home Gateway's password will not be checked.

l2FHomeGatewayReceivePassword.name: l2FHomeGatewayReceivePassword
l2FHomeGatewayReceivePassword.description: Password to expect from the Home Gateway when opening a tunnel. If left blank, then the Home Gateway's password will not be checked.

l2FHomeGatewaySendChecksum.name: l2FHomeGatewaySendChecksum
l2FHomeGatewaySendChecksum.description: Include Checksum field in transmitted L2F frames

l2FHomeGatewayCheckChecksum.name: l2FHomeGatewayCheckChecksum
l2FHomeGatewayCheckChecksum.description: Check Checksum field in received L2F frames

l2FHomeGatewaySendUDPChecksum.name: l2FHomeGatewaySendUDPChecksum
l2FHomeGatewaySendUDPChecksum.description: Calculate and include UDP checksum in transmitted L2F frames

l2FHomeGatewayEchoInterval.name: l2FHomeGatewayEchoInterval
l2FHomeGatewayEchoInterval.description: Time (in seconds) between L2F Echo Request frames sent to the Home Gateway to determine if it is still responding. These frames will only be sent when no packets are received from the Home Gateway. 0 indicates that Echo frames will not be used to determine if the Home Gateway is responding.

l2FHomeGatewayEchoRetries.name: l2FHomeGatewayEchoRetries
l2FHomeGatewayEchoRetries.description: The number of unanswered L2F Echo Request frames that will be sent to the Home Gateway before declaring the tunnel dead.

l2TPLNSTable.description: Layer-2 Tunneling Protocol Network Server Information.

l2TPLNSKeyValue.description: The Key for this instance of the object in the Resource Manager tree.

l2TPLNSSourceIPAddress.name: l2TPLNSSourceIPAddress
l2TPLNSSourceIPAddress.description: Source IP address for L2TP control messages and data packets that we send to this LNS. If this is not configured, then we will use the sourceIpAddress from the VPOP configuration. If that is not configured, then we will use the mgmt_addr from the ip_services configuration.

l2TPLNSSendName.name: l2TPLNSSendName
l2TPLNSSendName.description: Name to send as the Host name in the L2TP Start Control Channel Reqest packet to open a tunnel

l2TPLNSSharedSecret.name: l2TPLNSSharedSecret
l2TPLNSSharedSecret.description: Shared Secret to use when opening a tunnel to the LNS. Used to authenticate the LNS and to authenticate ourselves to the LNS. Also used to encrypt certain AVPs such as the user name and PAP password. If left blank, tunnel authentication and AVP encryption will be disabled.

l2TPLNSEnableUDPChecksum.name: l2TPLNSEnableUDPChecksum
l2TPLNSEnableUDPChecksum.description: Calculate and include UDP checksum in transmitted L2TP data packets.

l2TPLNSHelloInterval.name: l2TPLNSHelloInterval
l2TPLNSHelloInterval.description: Time (in seconds)that must pass without any user data or control messages exchanged between the LAC and the LNS in oder for us to begin sending L2TP Hello messages to the LNS in order to determine if it is still responding. This time also specifies the duration between the transmitted L2TP Hello messages. Setting this to 0 will disable transmission of Hello messages to the LNS.

l2TPLNSInitialAckTimeout.name: l2TPLNSInitialAckTimeout
l2TPLNSInitialAckTimeout.description: Time (in seconds) to wait for an acknowledgment of a control message sent to the LNS. If this times out, the timeout value will be doubled for subsequent timeouts (up to the value of MaxAckTimeout) until the limit on the number of retries is reached. This value must be less than the value for MaxAckTimeout.

l2TPLNSMaxAckTimeout.name: l2TPLNSMaxAckTimeout
l2TPLNSMaxAckTimeout.description: Maximum Time (in seconds) to wait for an acknowledgment of a control message sent to the LNS. As acknowledgements timeout, the timeout value is doubled each time until this limit is reached. This value must be more than the value for InitialAckTimeout.

l2TPLNSCtrlMsgRetries.name: l2TPLNSCtrlMsgRetries
l2TPLNSCtrlMsgRetries.description: When L2TP control messages are not acknowledged by the LNS, this specifies the number of times to retry before declaring the tunnel dead.

l2TPLNSCtrlMsgRxWindow.name: l2TPLNSCtrlMsgRxWindow
l2TPLNSCtrlMsgRxWindow.description: This is the Receive Window Size that we sent to the LNS during tunnel establishment. It specifies the number of L2TP Ctrl Messages the LNS is allowed to send to us without receiving an acknowledgement from us.

virtualLinkConfigChannelDelineation.description: For the given HDLC channel, flag sequence insertion and bit stuffing is performed on the data stream. If set to TRUE, then flag sequence insertion and bit stuffing is performed

virtualLinkConfigChannelCRCType.description: HDLC channel CRC generation for outgoing data stream. CRC type is ignored when ChannelDelineation is FALSE

virtualLinkConfigChannelIdle.name: virtualLinkConfigChannelIdle
virtualLinkConfigChannelIdle.description: Indicates that the HDLC channel should use flag bytes or HDLC idle as the interframe time fill between HDLC packets.

virtualLinkConfigChannelFCSInvert.name: virtualLinkConfigChannelFCSInvert
virtualLinkConfigChannelFCSInvert.description: Controls the inversion of the FCS field inserted into the transmit packet. If set to TRUE, the FCS field in the outgoing HDLC stream is logically inverted. (NA for SCC)

virtualLinkConfigChannelDataInvert.name: virtualLinkConfigChannelDataInvert
virtualLinkConfigChannelDataInvert.description: Controls the HDLC processor to logically invert the outgoing HDLC data stream. If set to TRUE, the outgoing HDLC stream is logically inverted. (NA for SCC)

virtualLinkConfigChannelChannelisedLink.name: virtualLinkConfigChannelChannelisedLink
virtualLinkConfigChannelChannelisedLink.description: HDLC Channel Channelise Link.(T1 Only. Currently Not Supported)

virtualLinkConfigChannelByteSyncLink.name: virtualLinkConfigChannelByteSyncLink
virtualLinkConfigChannelByteSyncLink.description: This attribute is ignored if ChannelChannelisedLink is TRUE. (NA for SCC)

virtualLinkConfigChannelRate.name: virtualLinkConfigChannelRate
virtualLinkConfigChannelRate.description: Indicates the rate of each individual DS0. (NA for SCC).

virtualLinkConfigChannelQueueDepth.name: virtualLinkConfigChannelQueueDepth
virtualLinkConfigChannelQueueDepth.description: Internal queue depth for data to be transmitted by this Channel. Once queue depth is reached, data will be dropped until queue depth empties beyond this value. Data dropped is clipped from end of queue.

modemConfigDetectDefault.description: The default protocol the modem should assume if either 1) it fails to detect the remote caller's protocol, or 2) detection is turned off in the configuration.

pppConfigConnectLimit.name: pppConfigConnectLimit
pppConfigConnectLimit.description: Overall connection time limit (in minutes, 0 = no limit)

pppConfigInactivityLimit.name: pppConfigInactivityLimit
pppConfigInactivityLimit.description: Maximum inactivity time (in minutes) before user is disconnected (0 = no limit)

pppConfigMonitorTxActivity.name: pppConfigMonitorTxActivity
pppConfigMonitorTxActivity.description: If an inactivity limit is set, specifies whether transmitted packets (sent to the remote caller) should be monitored for activity. If set to false, then transmitted data is ignored, and cannot keep the call up.

pppConfigMonitorRxActivity.name: pppConfigMonitorRxActivity
pppConfigMonitorRxActivity.description: If an inactivity limit is set, specifies whether received packets (sent by the remote caller) should be monitored for activity. If set to false, then received data is ignored, and cannot keep the call up.

pppConfigCountRIP.name: pppConfigCountRIP
pppConfigCountRIP.description: Specifies whether RIP frames should count as activity, and thus should reset the inactivity timer

pppConfigCountPings.name: pppConfigCountPings
pppConfigCountPings.description: Specifies whether ICMP Echo Request and Echo Reply (ping) frames should count as activity, and thus should reset the inactivity timer

pppConfigCountIGMP.name: pppConfigCountIGMP
pppConfigCountIGMP.description: Specifies whether IGMP frames should count as activity, and thus should reset the inactivity timer

pppConfigUseEchoes.name: pppConfigUseEchoes
pppConfigUseEchoes.description: Send periodic LCP Echo-Request frames to detect dead links

pppConfigSendID.name: pppConfigSendID
pppConfigSendID.description: Send LCP Identification frame when LCP negotiation begins

pppConfigSendTimeRemaining.name: pppConfigSendTimeRemaining
pppConfigSendTimeRemaining.description: Send periodic LCP Time-Remaining frames to inform remote peer of connection time limit

pppConfigSendMRU.name: pppConfigSendMRU
pppConfigSendMRU.description: Include the Maximum-Receive-Unit option in transmitted LCP Configure-Request frames, informing remote peer of local MRU value

pppConfigSendACCM.name: pppConfigSendACCM
pppConfigSendACCM.description: Include the Asynchronous-Control-Character-Map option in transmitted LCP Configure-Request frames, informing remote peer of control characters it must escape when transmitting

pppConfigSendMagic.name: pppConfigSendMagic
pppConfigSendMagic.description: Include the Magic-Number option in transmitted LCP Configure-Request frames

pppConfigSendPFC.name: pppConfigSendPFC
pppConfigSendPFC.description: Include the Protocol-Field-Compression option in transmitted LCP Configure-Request frames, allowing the remote peer to compress the protocol field when transmitting

pppConfigSendACFC.name: pppConfigSendACFC
pppConfigSendACFC.description: Include the Address-and-Control-Field-Compression option in transmitted LCP Configure-Request frames, allowing the remote peer to compress the protocol field when transmitting, allowing the remote peer to omit the Address and Control fields when transmitting

pppConfigSendShortSeq.name: pppConfigSendShortSeq
pppConfigSendShortSeq.description: Include the Multilink Short Sequence Number option in transmitted LCP Configure-Request frames, allowing peer to transmit MLP frames with short (12-bit) sequence numbers

pppConfigSendEndpointDisc.name: pppConfigSendEndpointDisc
pppConfigSendEndpointDisc.description: Include the Multilink Endpoint Discriminator option in transmitted LCP Configure-Request frames

pppConfigAllowMRU.name: pppConfigAllowMRU
pppConfigAllowMRU.description: Allow the remote peer to specify its Maximum-Receive-Unit value in LCP Configure-Request frames it transmits

pppConfigAllowACCM.name: pppConfigAllowACCM
pppConfigAllowACCM.description: Allow the remote peer to include its Asynchronous-Control-Character-Map value in LCP Configure-Request frames its transmits

pppConfigAllowMagic.name: pppConfigAllowMagic
pppConfigAllowMagic.description: Allow the remote peer to include its Magic-Number value in LCP Configure-Request frames it transmits

pppConfigAllowPFC.name: pppConfigAllowPFC
pppConfigAllowPFC.description: Allow the remote peer to include the Protocol-Field-Compression option in LCP Configure-Request frames it transmits, allowing the local interface to compress the protocol field when transmitting

pppConfigAllowACFC.name: pppConfigAllowACFC
pppConfigAllowACFC.description: Allow the remote peer to include the Address-and-Control-Field-Compression option in LCP Configure-Request frames it transmits, allowing the remote peer to compress the protocol field when transmitting, allowing the local interface to omit the Address and Control fields when transmitting

pppConfigAllowShortSeq.name: pppConfigAllowShortSeq
pppConfigAllowShortSeq.description: Allow the peer to include the Multilink Short Sequence Number option in LCP Configure-Request frames it transmits, instructing the local interface to transmit MLP frames with short (12-bit) sequence numbers

pppConfigAllowEndpointDisc.name: pppConfigAllowEndpointDisc
pppConfigAllowEndpointDisc.description: Allow the remote peer to include the Multilink Endpoint Discriminator option in LCP Configure-Request frames it transmits

pppConfigLCPRestartTimer.name: pppConfigLCPRestartTimer
pppConfigLCPRestartTimer.description: Time (in milliseconds) between unanswered LCP Configure-Request frames

pppConfigPassiveLCP.name: pppConfigPassiveLCP
pppConfigPassiveLCP.description: Don't send an LCP Configure-Request frame until either the peer has sent one, or a short timeout has expired

pppConfigPassiveLCPTimeout.name: pppConfigPassiveLCPTimeout
pppConfigPassiveLCPTimeout.description: The amount of time (in milliseconds) that LCP will wait for the peer to send a Configure-Request before sending one

pppConfigMinRemoteMRU.name: pppConfigMinRemoteMRU
pppConfigMinRemoteMRU.description: Minimum acceptable value for Max-Receive-Unit specified by remote peer

pppConfigMinLocalMRU.name: pppConfigMinLocalMRU
pppConfigMinLocalMRU.description: Minimum acceptable value for Max-Receive-Unit for local interface

pppConfigPeerNSStrategy.name: pppConfigPeerNSStrategy
pppConfigPeerNSStrategy.description: Specifies how DNS/NBNS values suggested by peer will be handled. They will either be Config-Rejected (Reject), Config-Acked (Ack), or ignored and negotiated with Config-Nak with the configured values (Ignore).

pppConfigMLPMaxFragments.description: Maximum number of MLP fragments that a transmit frame will be divided into

pppConfigMLPScaleFragments.name: pppConfigMLPScaleFragments
pppConfigMLPScaleFragments.description: Should Multilink fragment sizes depend on the relative speed of the links?

pppConfigMLPSendNullFragments.name: pppConfigMLPSendNullFragments
pppConfigMLPSendNullFragments.description: Should Multilink periodically send null fragments to help the remote peer in discarding dead fragments?

pppConfigMLPNullFragmentTimeout.description: The amount of time (in seconds) between null Multilink fragments sent to the remote peer. This value is valid only if this feature is enabled.

pppConfigMLPEndpointDisc.name: pppConfigMLPEndpointDisc
pppConfigMLPEndpointDisc.description: Specifies the type of Endpoint Discriminator the CVX should send when negotiating Multilink. pppConfigMLPGroupNumber.name: pppConfigMLPGroupNumber
pppConfigMLPGroupNumber.description: Multilink group number. This is valid only when the MLP endpoint discriminator type is set to GroupNumber. This should only be configured when you have been instructed to do so by a Nortel Networks employee.

pppConfigLogEnabled.name: pppConfigLogEnabled
pppConfigLogEnabled.description: Specifies whether PPP events should be logged

pppConfigLogSize.name: pppConfigLogSize
pppConfigLogSize.description: Number of events in the PPP log buffer. Each log event requires 24 bytes of memory; the default of 128 requires 3K of memory per call.

pppConfigLogControlFrames.name: pppConfigLogControlFrames
pppConfigLogControlFrames.description: If PPP logging is enabled, specifies whether transmitted and received control frames should be logged. Control frames include LCP and IPCP frames. This should always be on.

pppConfigLogProtocolFrames.name: pppConfigLogProtocolFrames
pppConfigLogProtocolFrames.description: If PPP logging is enabled, specifies whether transmitted and received protocol frames should be logged. Protocol frames include all IP frames (UDP, TCP, DNS, etc.). This should always be on.

pppConfigLogOptions.name: pppConfigLogOptions
pppConfigLogOptions.description: If PPP logging is enabled, specifies whether PPP negotiation options should be logged. This is particularly useful for diagnosing PPP connection problems.

pppConfigLogStates.name: pppConfigLogStates
pppConfigLogStates.description: If PPP logging is enabled, specifies whether PPP events and state transitions should be logged. This is sometimes useful in diagnosing PPP connection problems.

pppConfigLogCompression.name: pppConfigLogCompression
pppConfigLogCompression.description: If PPP logging is enabled, specifies whether PPP data compression events should be logged. This is useful in diagnosing compression performance problems.

pppConfigLogMLP.name: pppConfigLogMLP
pppConfigLogMLP.description: If PPP logging is enabled, specifies whether PPP Multilink events should be logged. This is useful in diagnosing multilink performance problems.

pppConfigLogVJ.name: pppConfigLogVJ
pppConfigLogVJ.description: If PPP logging is enabled, specifies whether PPP VJ header compression events should be logged. This is useful in diagnosing TCP/IP performance problems when VJ header compression is enabled and negotiated.

pppConfigCCPEnabled.name: pppConfigCCPEnabled
pppConfigCCPEnabled.description: Specifies whether the Compression Control Protocol (RFC 1962) is enabled. Note that enabling CCP does not automatically cause the CVX to compress frames it transmits; that is controlled by the CompressFrames entry. This configuration was split into two options because many common client implementations of CCP can take over 30 seconds to connect when CCP is disabled. To get these clients to connect quickly, set CCPEnabled to 'true'. To prevent the CVX from actually compressing the data, set CompressFrames to 'false.'

pppConfigCompressFrames.name: pppConfigCompressFrames
pppConfigCompressFrames.description: Compress transmitted frames when CCP has been negotiated. Set this to 'false' to prevent the CVX from compressing frames, even when CCP is enabled and negotiated successfully.

pppConfigIPXCPEnabled.name: pppConfigIPXCPEnabled
pppConfigIPXCPEnabled.description: IPX Control Protocol enabled. For use with DVS tunnels only.

pppConfigIPXNetworkNumber.name: pppConfigIPXNetworkNumber
pppConfigIPXNetworkNumber.description: IPX network number to assign to remote user. For use with DVS tunnels only.

pppConfigIPXNodeNumber.name: pppConfigIPXNodeNumber

policyConfigModemFailCount.description: The number of failed connections a modem can have in a sampling period (specified elsewhere) before it will be taken out of service. For example, if this number is set to 8, and the sample count is set to 16, then a modem that fai ls more than 8 out of its last 16 connection attempts will be taken out of service. 0 indicates that the modem will never be taken out of service for this reason.

If a modem fails more times in this sampling period than allowed, then it is taken out of service. frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLMIType.description: This variable states which Data Link Connec- tion Management scheme is active on the Frame Relay interface.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiAddress.description: This variable states which address format is in use on the Frame Relay interface. Currently, on Q922 is supported.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiAddressLen.description: This variable states which address length in octets. In the case of Q922 format, the length indicates the entire length of the address including the control portion. Currently, on 2 octet address are supported

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiPollingInterval.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiPollingInterval
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiPollingInterval.description: This is the number of seconds between successive status enquiry messages. This is equivalent to T391.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiFullEnquiryInter.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiFullEnquiryInter.description: Number of status enquiry intervals that pass before issuance of a full status enquiry message. This is equivalent to N391.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiErrorThreshold.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiErrorThreshold
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiErrorThreshold.description: This is the maximum number of unanswered Status Enquiries the equipment shall accept before declaring the interface down. This is equivalent to N392.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMonitoredEvents.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMonitoredEvents
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMonitoredEvents.description: This is the number of status polling intervals over which the error threshold is counted. For example, if within 'MonitoredEvents' number of events the station receives 'ErrorThreshold' number of errors, the interface is marked as down. This is equivalent to N393.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.description: The maximum number of Virtual Circuits allowed for this interface. Usually dictated by the Frame Relay network. Currently, any DLCI dictated by the Frame Relay network will not be enabled unless that frCircuitEntry is configured.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMulticast.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMulticast
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMulticast.description: This indicates whether the Frame Relay interface is using a multicast service

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLinkType.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLinkType
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLinkType.description: This indicates whether the Frame Relay interface is the Network-side of a UNI (UNI-DCE), User-side of a UNI (UNI-DTE) or a Network-Network Inteface (NNI).

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxLogIntf.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxLogIntf
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxLogIntf.description: Maximum number of Logical Interfaces supported on this Frame Relay Interface

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLinkEnable.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLinkEnable
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLinkEnable.description: Specifies whether this interface is to be activated.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLMIFlowControl.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLMIFlowControl
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLMIFlowControl.description: Specifies whether LMI based (R-bit) notification performs flow control for the Circuits on this interface.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiBECNFlowControl.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiBECNFlowControl
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiBECNFlowControl.description: Specifies whether BECN notification performs flow control for the Circuits on this interface.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLMIBandwidthCont.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLMIBandwidthControl
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLMIBandwidthCont.description: Specifies whether LMI based CIR notification affects the CIR flow control parameters for the circuits on this interface.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiInjectionManagem.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiInjectionManagement
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiInjectionManagem.description: Specifies whether injection management (for holding data to prevent exceeding excess rates) is enabled on all circuits on this interface.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxFrameSize.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxFrameSize
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiMaxFrameSize.description: Specifies maximum frame size allowed on this interface, including data link headers.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLmiDlci.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLmiDlci
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiLmiDlci.description: The dlci upon which LMI traffic will be broadcast.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiDceErrorThreshol.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiDceErrorThreshold
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiDceErrorThreshol.description: This is the maximum number of unanswered Status Enquiries the equipment shall accept before declaring the interface down. This is equivalent to N392.

frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiDceMonitoredEven.name: frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiDceMonitoredEvents
frInterfaceConfigFrDlcmiDceMonitoredEven.description: This is the number of status polling intervals over which the error threshold is counted. For example, if within 'MonitoredEvents' number of events the station receives 'ErrorThreshold' number of errors, the interface is marked as down. This is equivalent to N393.

frCircuitConfigFrCircuitDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier for this virtual circuit.

frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCommittedBurst.name: frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCommittedBurst
frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCommittedBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to transfer under normal conditions, during the measurement interval. If Bc > 0, then CIR must be set to a non-zero value

frCircuitConfigFrCircuitExcessBurst.name: frCircuitConfigFrCircuitExcessBurst
frCircuitConfigFrCircuitExcessBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will attempt to deliver over the measurement interval. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, the Excess Information Burst Size is set to the value of ifSpeed.

frCircuitConfigFrCircuitThroughput.name: frCircuitConfigFrCircuitThroughput
frCircuitConfigFrCircuitThroughput.description: Throughput is the average number of 'Frame Relay Information Field' bits transferred per second across a user network interface in one direction, measured over the measurement interval. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both non-zero, the measurement interval, T, is T=frCircuitCommittedBurst/frCircuitThroughput. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both zero, the measurement interval, T, is T=frCircuitExcessBurst/ifSpeed. If CIR > 0, then Bc must be set to a non-zero value

frCircuitConfigFrCircuitMulticast.name: frCircuitConfigFrCircuitMulticast
frCircuitConfigFrCircuitMulticast.description: This indicates whether this VC is used as a unicast VC (i.e. not multicast). Currently, if not unicast, then multicast.

frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCommittedBurstMi.name: frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCommittedBurstMin
frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCommittedBurstMi.description: This variable indicates the minimum bound for the variable hjCircuitCommittedBurst. If a SET is received to this variable above the value of the variable CircuitCommittedBurst, the agent should respond bad-Value.

frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCongestionMonito.name: frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCongestionMonitorPeriod
frCircuitConfigFrCircuitCongestionMonito.description: The measurement interval for the Congestion Monitor, which determines whether to raise or lower the Commited Information Rate. This period is expressed in 100ths of a second.

ethernetConfigEthernetLinkTest.description: Configures the port to be, for 10BASE-T, to disable Link Test Functionality which is used to determine link integrity by listening for link beat pulses. Setting this attribute will disable link beat pulse detection.

rbsConfigDid.description: Enable Direct Inward Dial. When true, digits are collected to determine the called address. When false, no digits are collected.

rbsConfigAllowNoDigits.description: Determines the action taken when Direct Inward Dial is configured, but no resources are available to collect the digits. If true, then calls are accepted without the called address information. If false, then busy is re turned

rbsConfigDod.name: rbsConfigDod
rbsConfigDod.description: Enable Direct Outward Dial. When true, digits are sent for outgoing calls. When false, no digits are sent

rbsConfigGlareResolve.description: Determines the action taken when glare (collision between incoming and outgoing call) is detected. If true, the glare is resolved by abandoning the outgoing call. If false, the outgoing call is preserved, and the far si de is assumed to abandon the incoming call

rbsConfigOOS.name: rbsConfigOOS

rbsConfigBusyOutOOS.name: rbsConfigBusyOutOOS
